Today, the President will present the National Medal of Science to ten researchers and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation to three individuals and a three-person team. These medals are the highest honors given by the United States government to scientists, engineers, and inventors. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made significant contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation honors those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The recipients and their achievements are listed in the article.